reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Gym bag
reviews.reviewText: I like its design, especially the wet pockets and shoe compartment. The front and the internal pockets are helpful to get your items well-organized. lightweight itself and seems sturdy so far. Highly recommend it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bag for an overnight trip.
reviews.reviewText: My hubby gave this to me for a gym bag, however it’s too big for the lockers at my gym. I had been wanting an overnight traveling bag and was able to use it last week when we were out of town for 5 days. It held my shoes, lingerie, pj’s and socks. It was perfect and made it easy to pack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Overall very good gym bag
reviews.reviewText: A lot of separate compartments with individual zippers. Including several good for wet gear. Plenty of room but the fact that it's kind of flimsy actually is a good thing. It easily just collapses to whatever you have in the bag. Plenty of room for gym, change of all clothes and shoes too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Super great bag
reviews.reviewText: Plenty of room for everything I need for the gym. Lightweight but seemingly durable. Very happy with the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Gym Bag!
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a small gym bag that would hold all my essentials, but also be small enough to fit in a locker at the gym. This bag does both. The material is great and sturdy, the wet pocket is a great addition and my size 11.5M shoes fit perfect in the shoe compartment. Exactly what I was looking for!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small cute and functional
reviews.reviewText: Love this gym bag. Fits tennis shoes and a change of clothes plus all my swim gear. Love the wet pocket for my bathing suit and the separate shoe compartment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great gym bag
reviews.reviewText: Love the shoe pocket, fits my work boots no problem and still has plenty of room inside. The cup holder is nice too, fits a small shaker bottle exactly. Only issue is that it has no bottom support so it sags.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love this bag. It is amazing. Its perfect size and is just what I needed it for. I started a new job and they have a gym facility on-site. So, I needed some type of bag to take so I can shower and change clothes before starting work. This bag was the perfect buy. I can store my shoes, size 11 -mens, in the side compartment. With still plenty of room for my change of clothes and shower bag. It fits perfectly in the lockers where I store it while I am working out. It feels really light when carrying across my shoulder which is great as well. Some bags can cause some pressure on the top shoulder near the clavicle which becomes painful over time. Not this bag. This bag has proven to be nothing but shoulder comfort. Thank you for making such a great product. And the price is amazing! Why pay for a name on a bag that is more than likely not ergonomical to carry around when you can pay for a better product that is? I am only using it for the gym. If thats all you plan on using it for then this is the perfect product that I would highly recommend.Thanks.
